National Security Advisor Jake Sullivan held a virtual meeting with Burmese National Unity Government (NUG) representatives Duwa Lashi La and Zin Mar Aung. They discussed the pro-democracy movement in Burma and efforts to restore democracy. Sullivan expressed concern over the violent actions of the Burmese military and emphasized U.S. support for accountability for the coup. The recent arrest of pro-democracy activist Ko Jimmy was also discussed, with the U.S. advocating for his release and that of others unjustly detained. Regional and international engagement, as well as U.S. support for ASEAN efforts to hold the military regime accountable, were also touched upon. The COVID-19 pandemic in Burma and ongoing U.S. humanitarian assistance were highlighted, with Sullivan affirming continued support for the people of Burma.